# --- Changelog #6 ( 3/8/2026 | 12:54pm/24:54 EST | v0.3.0 ) --- #

- Added Dynamic Hands:
    * Visible hands that change their finger highlight based on key press required.
    * Updated README file.
- Added Additional Settings.
    * Settings for week specific typing lessons.
- Added More Strings:
    * Added a few more words, phrases, and sentences.
- Fixed Keyboard Bugs:
    * Fixed some keys that would not show up properly being highlighted.

# ! ---> Changelog #5 ( 3/6/2026 | 09:00pm/21:00 EST | v0.2.0 ) <--- ! #
NOTE: Features discussed in previous changelogs are accurate, however some additional changes were not written down. This is all of the important/up-to-date compiled information here.

- Added Settings Checkboxes:
    * Enables/Disables options in settings.
- Added Settings Input Box:
    * Set the value of skipping repeats up till 50.
- Created dynamic keyboard:
    * Displays what the user needs to input next.
    * Text remains big no matter the size.
    * Adjusts as needed for screen size.
- Revamped the CSS and HTML layout of the web-app.
    * Increased border of containers and buttons to make them stand out more.
    * Keyboard integration (look at bullet point above).
    * Restart button now auto-focuses on input box alongside setting repeat_list to zero (maybe make a setting?).
    * Settings looks cleaner (still need to add buttons).
    * Better text scaling for when the windows gets bigger or smaller.
    * Added Autoscrolling when typing.
    * Gradient background.
    * Settings layout changed.
- Code Comments:
    * Added more comments in code.
    * Removed unnecessary ones.
- Website Scaling:
    * Improved on the scaling of the website, making it more clean.
- Patched Recursion Bug:
    * Fixed an issue with infinite recursion when dev testing (when only a certain amount of attempts are possible due to word-bank.js being limited).
    * Fixed a line so it also includes the setting as a condition.
- Updated Changelog:
    * Major inconsistencies with previous changelog data, so I have compiled all of them here for what has been done so far:

    * Created & reformatted README:
        a. README now has a nice looking display on GitHub with a bunch of details about the project.
        b. New images for README content.
    * Created changelog:
        a. Made a changelog file to track changes made.
        b. Contains proper time and date format.
        c. Went back to previous changelogs to include time and date.
    * Added an images folder.
        a. Contains screenshots/mock-up images.
    * Added options:
        a. Created a "Settings" button on the bottom-right.
        b. Highlight Word: underlines and colors the current character blue.
        c. Disable Score: disables the component from showing up on screen (still secretly tracked).
        d. Restart Score: score gets reset when the "Reset" button is clicked (still changes displayed text).
        e. Skip Repeats: store an array of previously answered attempts and ensure they are not shown until they are removed from the list.
        f. Store Skip Repeats: stores up to <int> of attempts in an array before discarding the first entry.
        g. Skip With Errors: can finish an attempt incorrectly (subtracts a point).
        h. Disappearing Text: hides characters you've completed correctly.
    * Website scaling:
        a. Made it so the website scales a bit better when shrinking window size and components don't freak out.
    * Logic changes:
        a. Changed how spans and input are read so I can make the visuals more cohesive (scaling the page will work pretty well with odd window sizes).

